cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of SDN capabilities in networking equipment to implement energy saving algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of an ONOS application to realize an energy-aware traffic scheduler. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to implementing energy saving algorithms. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the use of distributed computing to implement energy saving algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper may touch upon information theory concepts related to optimizing energy consumption in telecommunication infrastructure.
